# Manual grant tracker
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Grants you are actively tracking, drafting, or have submitted.
# These are ALWAYS surfaced in the digest regardless of LLM relevance score.
# The LLM will still score them and generate a summary + recommended next step,
# which is useful for planning — but they will never be filtered out.
#
# Copy this file to manual_grants.yaml and edit. Add as many entries as needed.
#
# Fields:
#   title       (required)  Display name for the grant
#   funder      (required)  Funding agency, e.g. SSHRC, NSERC, CFI, Tri-Agency
#   program                 Specific program name
#   amount                  Expected or maximum award as a plain string
#   deadline    (required)  Application deadline in YYYY-MM-DD format.
#                           Entries with past deadlines are automatically hidden.
#   link                    URL to the program page or competition notice
#   status      (required)  One of: tracking | drafting | submitted | awarded | declined
#   notes                   Free-form context: eligibility notes, partner contacts,
#                           LOI dates, internal decision points. Passed to the LLM
#                           as the grant summary so be as detailed as helpful.

grants:

  - title: SSHRC Insight Development Grant
    funder: SSHRC
    program: Insight Development Grant
    amount: Up to $75,000 over 2 years
    deadline: "2026-10-15"
    link: https://www.sshrc-crsh.gc.ca/funding-financement/programs-programmes/insight_development_grants-subventions_de_developpement_savoir-eng.aspx
    status: tracking
    notes: >
      IDG for emerging researchers developing new research questions or testing
      new methodologies. Budget ceiling $75k over 2 years.
      Requires CCV, research proposal, budget justification.
      Check competition notice for current deadline — listed date is approximate.

  - title: NSERC Discovery Grant
    funder: NSERC
    program: Discovery Grants Program — Individual
    amount: Varies; typical ecology awards $25,000–$80,000/year
    deadline: "2026-11-01"
    link: https://www.nserc-crsng.gc.ca/Professors-Professeurs/grants-subs/dgigp-psigp_eng.asp
    status: tracking
    notes: >
      Annual competition with November 1 deadline for most disciplines.
      Requires full application package including CCV, research proposal,
      contributions to training, and HQP details.

  - title: NSERC Alliance Grant
    funder: NSERC
    program: Alliance
    amount: $150,000–$1M+ depending on partner contributions
    deadline: "2026-05-15"
    link: https://www.nserc-crsng.gc.ca/Professors-Professeurs/grants-subs/alliance-alliance_eng.asp
    status: drafting
    notes: >
      Requires formal non-profit or industry partner with cash or in-kind
      contributions. Grand River Conservation Authority or Nature Conservancy
      of Canada could be a fit. No LOI required; apply any time (rolling intake)
      but internal deadlines apply — confirm with research office.

  - title: CFI John R. Evans Leaders Fund
    funder: Canada Foundation for Innovation
    program: John R. Evans Leaders Fund (JELF)
    amount: Up to $500,000 (institution matches 40%)
    deadline: "2026-09-01"
    link: https://www.innovation.ca/apply-manage-awards/funding-opportunities/john-r-evans-leaders-fund/
    status: tracking
    notes: >
      For early-career researchers within 10 years of first faculty appointment.
      Must be nominated by WLU research office — confirm eligibility window.
      Covers research infrastructure (computing, equipment, field tools).
